## Prerequisites

Requirements:
- Java Development Kit (JDK)
- Maven
- Internet connection to access the Star Wars API


## Getting Started

To get a local copy up and running, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:
 - git clone https://github.com/your-username/spring-boot-star-wars-api.git

3. Build the project using Maven:
 - mvn clean install

4. Run the application:
 - mvn spring-boot:run

5. The application will start running on http://localhost:8080.


## Usage

Get All Characters
To retrieve information for all Star Wars characters, make a GET request to the following endpoint:
 - http://localhost:8080/api/characters

Get Character by ID
To retrieve information for a specific Star Wars character by ID, make a GET request to the following endpoint, replacing {id} with the ID of the character:
- http://localhost:8080/api/characters/{id}

Get All Names
To retrieve Names for all Star Wars characters, make a GET request to the following endpoint:
 - http://localhost:8080/api/characters/names

Get Character by Name
To retrieve information for a specific Star Wars character by name, make a GET request to the following endpoint, replacing {name} with the name of the character:
- http://localhost:8080/api/characters/name/{name}